---
description: Testing and accessibility conventions
globs: ["**/*.test.{ts,tsx}", "**/*.stories.{ts,tsx}"]
---

Testing stack: Vitest, Testing Library, user-event, and vitest-axe.

Required for every component:

- Axe test covering default render and each variant.
- Keyboard navigation test for applicable keys.
- Screen reader label test for aria-label, aria-labelledby, or aria-describedby.
- Focus management test where applicable.
- Use user-event for interactions, never fireEvent.
- Query by role, label, or text. Do not query by class name.

Stories serve as integration tests through Storybook and the test runner.

Accessibility gates block merges:

- jsx-a11y strict rule violations
- axe violations in unit tests
- axe violations in Storybook test runner
- pa11y-ci violations on the docs site
